review_blob: 750 ml bottle dated 04/05/2006. Lost in the back of the store for over 8 years.. It aged well, much like a champagne, but mildly tart and with excellent body. A bit of barnyard. Incredibly smooth and mellow behind the tartness. Beautiful lacing.

Pint at the brewpub, at a CASK meeting a few months ago.    Excellent rendition of a stout.  Black pour with brown head.  Flavors of roasty dark malts, coffee and dark chocolate, with a smooth creamy finish.  Very tasty.

Pint at the brewpub, at a CASK meeting a few months ago.   A well done take on a Black IPA.   Good hop aroma, roasty dark malts, with notes of dark chocolate, coffee.   Well hopped but not over the top, decent bitter finish,  very enjoyable.
Pint at the brewpub, at a CASK meeting a few months ago.    Good hop aroma from the dry hopping.    Flavor is a nice balance of caramel malts and hops with a mild bitter finish.  Excellent beer.
Pint at the brewpub, at a CASK meeting several months ago.   Sweet and fruity, good alcohol kick.   Pretty good tripel.
sample from 12oz bottle at the CASK brewclub meeting.    Pours black with brown head.  Aroma of dark roased malts and chocolate.  Flavors of dark roasted malts, chocolate, and coffee.  pretty good.
beer_name: The Duck-Rabbit Rabid Duck Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Sample from 750 at the CASK brewclub meeting.   Pours hazy ruby with small white head.   Aroma is sour cherry with some brett funk.   Flavor is sweet/sour cherry with brett, spicy wild yeast, and a touch of bitterness.  pretty good.

Sample from a 750ml bottle at a CASK Brewclub meeting.  Bright golden pour with lively carbonation and white head.  Very Belgian/Saison with spicy hops and orange.  A lot of flavor in this one.  A little tart and wheaty. Excellent.

Pint on tap at the brewery.  Dark beer with a small beige head.  Aroma is mildly roasty with a faint hint of peppers.  Flavor is a little roasty  but mild until about halfway through the glass when it warms the mouth and provides a fuller flavor and body.  Never gets hot from the peppers, very easy drinking.  Subtle and interesting.

Pint at the brewery tap room.   Pale amber beer with a medium white head.   Sweet pale malt and cascade hop aroma.  Flavor of sweet pale malt and citric cascade hops.  Everything pretty much as expected.  Enjoyable and tasty but not fabulous.
Pint at the brewery taproom.   Golden beer with white head.  Fruity citrus aroma.    Sweet fruity and spicy to start then dries out on the finish.  An excellent saison.
beer_name: Intuition Ale Works Shape Shifter Saison

review_blob: Pint at the brewery tap room.  Dark mahogany/black beer.  Citrus and roast in the aroma.  Prickly citric hops paired with the roasted malts and coffee flavors.  Centennial makes its presence known but not so brightly as in The Face.  Its a very tasty combination.  Really excellent.  I loved it.

Pint at the brewery tap room.   Aroma is citrus and pale malt.  Flavor also heavy on the citrus, pine resin, fruit, and a little bit sweet.  The Centennial really comes through and shines.   Excellent stuff.  I loved it.

12 oz bottle given to me by a friend.  Aroma of spiced apple pie.  Flavor also like eating spiced apple pie, but with a bit of artificial sweetener, and a wheaty, malty backing. Its decent for an apple pie fruit beer, but I couldnt drink more than one.

Pint on tap at Peles in Jacksonville.  Clear orange-amber beer with small white head.  Aroma of smoke with light notes of malt, leather, and spice.  Flavor is smoke and ash with caramel and a bit of fruit.  Smooth medium body and lightly hoppy finish.  Very tasty and drinkable smoke ale.  6.2% ABV.  Excellent.

sample from a 12oz bottle at the CASK Group Brew in Jacksonville, Feb 25, 2012.  Golden beer with a white head and aroma of Habanero.  I like hot and spicy, but you got to be nuts to drink this.  Far beyond any heat I am willing to put up with in a beer.  Novelty only.

sample from a 12oz bottle at the CASK Group Brew in Jacksonville, Feb 25, 2012.  Golden beer with a white head and aroma of Jalapeno and Habanero.  Interesting take on a chili beer.  Some heat but not too hot and plenty of chili flavor.  Smooth pale ale background.  A good effort.

sample from 750 bottle at the CASK Group Brew in Jacksonville, Feb 25, 2012.   Red-amber beer with a yeasty, sour aroma.   Flavor was strongly sour, malty with some funk.  Notes of cherry and plum.  Pretty good.
sample from 750 bottle at the CASK Group Brew in Jacksonville, Feb 25, 2012.   Light citric and sour aroma.  Flavor was yeasty, funky, sour citrus and spice.  Not too extreme and pretty good.

Sample from a bottle at the CASK brewclub meeting 2-11-2012, at Seven Bridges Grille, Jacksonville.   Yet another extremely well done west coast IPA.  Aroma of sweet malts and loads of hops. Flavor is strongly hop forward, piney, citric and bitter.  A bit dry and lighter abv than expected.  A great beer.

Pint on tap at Kickbacks, Jacksonville.  Dark amber beer with a light tan head.   Sweet Belgian aroma.  Flavor is smooth and lightly sweet with caramel and dark fruits.  Very enjoyable to drink, tasty and little hint of the high alcohol.  Excellent.

Pint on tap at Kickbacks, Jacksonville.   Good looking black beer with a small tan head.  Roasty, malty aroma.  Flavor was good, semi-sweet dark malts, coffee, and chocolates.  I had just finished a Smuttynose Baltic Porter, so this didnt taste so sweet in comparison.  An enjoyable stout in any case, very easy drinking and tasty.

Pint on tap at Kickbacks, Jacksonville.  Black beer with a nice thick brown head.  Chocolate and malt aroma.  Flavor is very sweet, stopped just short of being two sweet, but excellent for a baltic porter.  Very tasty with bold flavors of chocolate, coffee, and dark fruit. Full body and semi-thick mouthfeel.  Very well done, and a delightful desert drink.

Pint on tap at the Gainesville, Florida location.   My first visit to a BJs and I didnt have time to do it justice. Only had time for one beer and so I chose the holiday special which was the Grand Cru.  Beautiful orange beer with fluffy white head, fragrant aroma of Belgian yeast and orange.  The flavor was sweet with candy sugar, Belgian yeast and orange, and a bit of spice.  Deliciously drinkable in spite of the 10% abv which was well covered.  Surprisingly good for a brewpub offering.   I wish I had the time (and a driver) to be able to try the stout and IPA and a couple more.

Pint on tap at the brewery taproom.  Orange-amber beer with a white head.  light malt and hop aroma.  Flavor is dry pale ale with rye sharpness. Citric hop bitternes.  Im not really a fan of these rye beers and I dont understand the current rye beer fad.  This one is ok, maybe even good, but not great and not as good as the Magnum P. Rye.
beer_name: Bold City Archies Rhino Rye Pale Ale

review_blob: Pint at the brewery taproom.   A special 10 barrel brew for Thanksgiving.   Its billed as an Imperial Rye Pale Ale and that is exactly what it tastes like.   Very little aroma, but a good looking beer with a small white head.  Thick, chewy and malty backbone with a firm bitterness from the magnum hops.  A bit sharp from the Rye as well as the hops.   Alcohol not as noticeable as you would expect at 11%, but you can feel the buzz by the bottom of the glass.  The flavors stand out individually and each is easily discernible.   Not fabulous, but tasty and thoroughly enjoyable after a long day at work.

Pint glass at the brewery taproom.  This beer was the combined effort of Intuitions brewers and CASK club member Nathan Fulton, who won the Belgian beer category competition and the opportunity to brew 10 barrels of his beer at Intuition.  It was a fabulous recipe, with orange peel and grains of paradise spice in a belgian pale ale.  Fruity, spicy, malty, and a wonderful belgian funk made this beer absolutely delicious.  It was the best beer on the menu for the night (Oct 8).  Congratulations, Nathan and Ben for such a collaboration and a wonderful beer!

Pint at the brewery taproom after the CASK brewclub meeting on Nov 12.  ABV posted on the blackboard in the taproom was 5.5%   Dark brown/black beer with a small beige head.  Flavors of coffee and chocolate with just a bit of sweetness.  A fairly good porter. Enjoyable.

Pint glass at the brewery taproom.  Tried this beer on the night of the CASK club meeting, October 8.  I mostly wanted to see how my own homebrewed alt stacked up against it.  A clear, brown beer with a white head and sweet malty aroma. It was malty and a bit sweet, with a crisp sharpness.  I concluded yet again that my own brew was superior, with a more delicate chocolate malt flavor.  Of course all home brewers think their own brews are the best..   Overall a good brew but not great.
beer_name: Intuition Ale Works Knot Head Alt

review_blob: Enjoyed several pints at the brewery during the Third Anniversary Celebration.  It was the regular Dukes Brown Ale aged in Woodford Reserve Bourbon barrels.  The regular beer is a decent drink and the bourbon barrel aging adds a nice flavor.  It was a great party, an all-day affair with $2 pints, and plenty of food catered by Jolly Mon Catering.  Hundreds of people filled the parking lot and had a great time.  Im already looking forward to next years celebration.
beer_name: Bold City Dukes Cold Nose Brown Ale - Bourbon Aged

review_blob: 10 oz snifter glass at the brewery taproom.  ABV listed as 7.7 on the board at the taproom.  Enjoyed with my boss after a day of selling brewing supplies!  This was a great brew..  Its a beautiful red-brown with beige head, and a nice malty aroma.  The flavor is sweet malt and caramel with a little booze.  Not too sweet but just right, and delicious.  I didnt detect any coffee flavors, and I am a real coffee fiend.  Its what you expect and want in a Scotch Ale..  An excellent effort by Intuition Ale Works.  The only way it could have been better is if they served it in a real pint glass.

pint at the brewery taproom.  Had this while attending the October meeting of the CASK Homebrewers Club.  I mostly wanted to see how it compared to my own Kolsch homebrew.  It was OK, a reasonably good session beer.  However, I much prefer my own homebrew.  I suppose that is the position taken by most home brewers.  Prost!

330ml bottle.  $8.95 for a four pack at the navy exchange.    A mite expensive, but ultimately worth it.    Almost candy-like aroma of dark malt, coffee, and chocolate.   Body is smooth and thick, and chewy in the mouth.   Flavors of dark malt, coffee, sweet dark chocolate, toffee.  excellent alcohol wallop that you cant taste at all.  The bitterness is offset by more sweetness than in the regular extra stout.  In fact, this is what the regular extra stout should have been all along.   Quite excellent to drink, enough complexity to keep your attention, but an easy drinker, and yummy in flavor.   If I ever catch this on sale Ill fill my garage.

12 oz bottle.   Nice hop aroma.  Flavors of resinous hops, light tropical fruit with a sweet and mildly bitter finish.   Pine, grapefruit, mango, pineapple, with plenty of resinous and citric hops.  Excellent IPA, but not among the best Ive had.
beer_name: Cigar City Jai Alai India Pale Ale

review_blob: 12 oz bottle.  Not much aroma.  Roasted malts and chocolate with some light toffee and nuttiness.  Medium body beer, a touch of sweetness to start but more dry and bitter on the finish.  A good beer, but not exceptionally good.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Tumbler Autumn Brown Ale

review_blob: Pint at the brewery taproom.  Hazy orange beer with a white head, and pleasant aroma of Belgian Wit.   Soapy, Belgian yeast flavor, a little spicy and fruity.  Light on the abv with only about 4.8, but very tasty and decent medium to light body.  Fairly good.

12 oz bottle.  Had two of these straight from the bottle at a college alumni party (thats going back a lot of years).  Nice and light and refreshing for a party outdoors in the Florida summer. Pretty tasty, the ginger was not overpowering and meshed well.  Wont rock your world but anybody could drink this stuff.

Pint on tap at the brewery tap room.   Deep golden beer with a white head.  Pale malt and hops aroma.  This beer was thrown together with leftover grain of unknown origin and leftover hops of unknown origin to make a 9% beer with an IPA feel to it.  Fairly tasty and drinkable in spite of (or maybe because of) the 9%.  Its a one-time brew, but its good while it lasts.

Four pack of 12 oz bottles for $6.99 at ABC in Orange Park.   Lovely Cascade hop aroma.  Honey sweetness and then English IPA flavor and firm bitter finish.  Resiny hops are the focus.  This is good but its not spectacular.  Its also not skunked or stale or infected like what those other guys were drinking and rating.  A fairly extreme beer at an excellent price... very nice.

12 oz bottle, included in a Shipyard sampler 12-pack I picked up on sale at Winn-Dixie for $11.99   Its miserable hot already in Florida so this hit the spot.  Mild, crisp and refreshing.  Flavor has a touch of wheat, citrus & light fruit.  Not a lot going on but its just about right for a summer ale.  I usually dont like this style but this one seems ok.  Its a decent, though not memorable hot weather brew.

Pint at the brewery taproom.   This is the regular 1901 Red Ale brewed to 9% and aged several months in a Jack Daniels whiskey barrel.  I like this version better than the original.  The whiskey barrel gives a bourbon sweetness and smooths out the roasty flavors of the red ale.  Complex and very good.
beer_name: Bold City 1901 Red Ale - Bourbon Aged

review_blob: 750ml bottle given to me in 2008 by  an exchange student from China that we hosted for the Christmas vacation.  Bottle labeled 15% ABV instead of the 16% shown here.  Sour rice flavor and alcohol.  A little sweetness and light fruit.   Not great but not terrible.
beer_name: Sho Chiku Bai (Pine Bamboo Plum) Classic Sake

review_blob: Sample from a keg on tap at the Jacksonville Craft Beer Festival, 5-20-2011.  An excellent IPA, almost a Double IPA with 7.3% abv and heavy hop profile.  Six varieties of hops that blend smoothly into a well balanced beer, sweet crisp start and nicely bitter finish.

Sample from a 12 oz bottle at the Jacksonville Craft Beer Festival, 5-20-2011.  Not distributed in Florida yet, but should be by September according to the company rep.  Its an ok schwarzbier, but nothing exciting.  Very sessionable, almost a light beer at only 4.5%   Sort of a dark malt pilsener with very little of what makes Guinness notable.  Disappointing.

Sample from a 12 oz bottle at the Jacksonville Craft Beer Festival, 5-20-2011.  I love the Dales Pale Ale and the Old Chub, so this was a serious disappointment.  Made me think I was drinking a slightly better Budweiser.  Why Oskar Blues would feature this at a Craft Beer Fest is beyond me.
beer_name: Oskar Blues Mamas Little Yella Pils

review_blob: 12 oz bottle from a sampler 12-pack, $10.49 at the navy base.  For cheap beer this is pretty good.  Very mild and quaffable.  Has the expected bockbier malty flavor, and a very faint bitterness at the end.  Its a notch above the lawnmower beers of the sampler pack.

12 oz bottle, part of a sampler 12-pack, $10.49 at the Navy Base.  This beer was one of the weaker offerings.  Not bad but certainly not great.  Reminds me of Budweiser but the flavor is a little better.  Sweet malts, grain, and a lightly grassy finish.  Ill save the rest of this for the next time I mow the lawn.

Pint at the brewery tap room.   My first beer of the night and I wanted to start it off with a bang.  Mission accomplished.  Bright hazy golden beer whth a big white head.  Strong aroma of citric hops, very pleasing.  Very tasty with flavors of sweet pale malts, tropical fruits, pine, and grapefruit.  Excellent balance in a huge beer.  ABV listed as 8.74% on the bars display board. I enjoyed this one a lot.
Pint at the brewery tap room.  Intuitions take on a Irish Red Ale.  Not one of my favorite styles, and not one of my favorite beers from Intuition.  Its a good enough drink for what it is.
beer_name: Intuition Ale Works The Red Man

review_blob: Pint at the brewery tap room.  Dark amber beer with a small off white head.  Aroma of pale malts and earthy hops.  Flavor of pale or amber malts and very earthy hops.  ABV 6%   Almost no citrus hop as expected in a typical IPA, this one has a considerably different hop flavor profile.  A pretty tasty, though unusual IPA.
